.TH NETWATCH 1 "2026-07-14" "0.1.0" "NetWatch TUI Manual"
.SH NAME
netwatch \- Lightweight network usage monitor with TUI and CLI interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B netwatch
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B netwatch
is a client application that interacts with the SQLite database populated by the
.B netwatchd
daemon. It features a Terminal User Interface (TUI) with real-time speed rates,
historical usage graphs, interface summary lists, and data search/filtering.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B live
Launch the live monitor page directly.
.TP
.B today
Print a summary of today's network usage.
.TP
.B yesterday
Print a summary of yesterday's network usage.
.TP
.B interfaces
List active interfaces and status.
.TP
.B history
Show historical usage records.
.TP
.B daemon status|start|stop
Query or control the background daemon service.
.TP
